# Copy to .env.local and fill in. Vite exposes only VITE_-prefixed vars to the app.

# --- Clerk (phase 2 auth) ---
# Clerk publishable key. When SET, the app mounts <ClerkProvider> + the auth gate
# and attaches a bearer token to every /api/chat and /api/sessions request. When
# UNSET, the app runs in dev-principal mode (no token; the backend reads
# PENNY_DEV_*), which is how the phase-1a e2e harness and local dev work.
# VITE_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_...

# --- E2E (Playwright + @clerk/testing) ---
# Clerk test keys used by the auth e2e specs (frontend/e2e/*.spec.ts). Only the
# publishable key is exposed to the browser; the secret key is used by
# @clerk/testing's setup to mint testing tokens.
# CLERK_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_...
